<head>CONVERSATION</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">聊天</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>FREE AND NOT OFFICIAL DIALOGUE AMONG FRIENDS, TYPICALLY ABOUT IMORTANT QUESTIONS OF COMMON INTEREST.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[[[ 語 in 論語 is the relevant term. 世說新語 is a most relevant record.</p>
<p>But 語錄 are predominantly records of sayings rather than dialogues.</p>
<p>Records of inconsequential small-talk must be distinguished. They are certainly prominent in Ming literature, but not so much in evidence before. They are richly represented in Plato's dialogues.</p>
<p>Cf. sermo convivialis]]]</p>
        </div>
    </div>
